<p><strong>Background:</strong> We analyzed whether content length affects citation likelihood.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> Pages over 2,500 words receive <strong>1.6× more citations</strong> than pages under 800 words. The correlation is linear up to approximately 3,500 words, after which it saturates.</p>
