<h2>Finding #8: Named-Source Citations Increase Citation Odds by 2.1×</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> We tested whether inline attribution affects AI Overview citations.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> Pages that cite named sources within the body text (for example, "According to Ahrefs..." or "BrightLocal found that...") are <strong>2.1× more likely to be cited</strong> than pages that present facts without attribution.</p>
